import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Body_Mass__g_', kde=True, bins=20)
    median_body_mass = data['Body_Mass__g_'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_body_mass, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {median_body_mass:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of body mass among penguins?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    chart = sns.boxplot(x='Species', y='Beak_Length__mm_', data=data)
    chart.set_title('How does the beak length vary across different species of penguins?')
    chart.legend(title='Species', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
